OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPM should not appoint BBC  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchair, says Dimbleby       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Veteran broadcaster David Dimbleby has 
OL,6, said the BBC chairman should not be    
OL,7, decided by the prime minister,         
OL,8, following Richard Sharp's resignation. 
OL,10,FMr Dimbleby called for a "cross party" 
OL,11,Fpublic commission to make the final    
OL,12,Frecommendation.                        
OL,14,FMr Sharp resigned after breaking rules 
OL,15,Fover dealings with ex-PM Boris Johnson 
OL,16,Fbefore his appointment as BBC chair.   
OL,18,FThe role is currently decided through a
OL,19,F"fair and open competition", but the PM
OL,20,Fultimately has the final say.          
